ubx_message.name: UBX-MON-HW2
ubx_message.comment: This message is deprecated in this protocol version. Use UBX-MON-HW3 and UBX-MON-RF instead. Status of different aspects of the hardware such as Imbalance, Low-Level Configuration and POST Results. The first four parameters of this message represent the complex signal from the RF front end. The following rules of thumb apply: • The smaller the absolute value of the variable ofsI and ofsQ, the better. Ideally, the magnitude of the I-part (magI) and the Q-part (magQ) of the complex signal should be the same.

structure.name: UBX-MON-HW2
structure.description: Status of different aspects of the hardware, such as antenna, PIO/peripheral pins, noise level, automatic gain control (AGC)

fields.name: pinSel
fields.description: Mask of pins set as peripheral/PIO

fields.name: pinBank
fields.description: Mask of pins set as bank A/B

fields.name: pinDir
fields.description: Mask of pins set as input/output

fields.name: pinVal
fields.description: Mask of pins value low/high

fields.name: noisePerMS
fields.description: Noise level as measured by the GPS core

fields.name: agcCnt
fields.description: AGC Monitor, as percentage of maximum gain, range 0 to 8191 (100%)

fields.name: aStatus
fields.description: Status of the antenna supervisor state machine (0=INIT, 1=DONTKNOW, 2=OK, 3=SHORT, 4=OPEN)

fields.name: aPower
fields.description: Current power status of antenna (0=OFF, 1=ON, 2=DONTKNOW)

fields.name: flags
fields.description: Flags

bits.name: jammingState
bits.description: Output from jamming/interference monitor (0 = unknown or feature disabled or flag unavailable, 1 = ok - no significant jamming, 2 = warning - interference visible but fix OK, 3 = critical - interference visible and no fix). This flag is deprecated in protocol versions that support UBX-SEC-SIG (version 0x02) and always reported as 0; instead jammingState in UBX-SEC-SIG should be monitored.

bits.name: xtalAbsent
bits.description: RTC xtal has been determined to be absent (not supported for protocol versions less than 18.00)

fields.name: reserved0
fields.description: Reserved

fields.name: usedMask
fields.description: Mask of pins that are used by the virtual pin manager

fields.name: VP
fields.description: Array of pin mappings for each of the 17 physical pins

fields.name: cwSuppression
fields.description: CW interference suppression level, scaled (0 = no CW jamming, 255 = strong CW jamming)

fields.name: reserved1
fields.description: Reserved

fields.name: pinIrq
fields.description: Mask of pins value using the PIO Irq

fields.name: pullH
fields.description: Mask of pins value using the PIO pull high resistor

fields.name: pullL
fields.description: Mask of pins value using the PIO pull low resistor
